Biography

At Utah Tech 2022 (Sophomore): Played in 10 games with nine starts for the Trailblazers ... caught 26 passes for 287 yards ... had a career high 96 yards on three catches including a career long 72 yard reception against Sacramento State ... had a season high seven catches with a touch down against Weber State ... also saw time on special teams with 26 kick returns for 114 yards including a career long 45 yard retrun ... returned seven punts for 71 yards witha long of 40 yards

At Utah Tech Fall 2021 (COVID Freshman): Played in seven games with one start and finished with 18 receptions for 276 yards and two touchdowns … racked up 77 yards on four catches and his first TD of the year at UC Davis (9/18) … caught three passes for a career high 96 yards and a touchdown in the win vs. Fort Lewis (11/13) … also returned 13 kickoffs for a combined 303 yards, including a season high 33-yard return vs. Tarleton State (10/16).

At Utah Tech Spring 2021 (Freshman): Played in all five games and caught seven passes for 114 yards … Three of his seven receptions went for touchdowns, two of those came in the fourth quarter at home vs. Tarleton (49 and 14 yards; 3/13), which were his only two receptions of the game … was also DSU’s top kick-off and punt returner … ran back five punts for 56 yards (11.2 ypr) and returned seven kick-offs for 103 yards (14.7 ypr).

At Yucaipa High School: Was a varsity letter winner in both football and track and field ... football stats and highlights are not available ... graduated in June 2020.

Personal: Born in Yucaipa, California … parents are Anthony and Casey Fisher ... father Anthony ran cross country collegiately … also recruited by Idaho State ... favorite team is the New Orleans Saints ... currently majoring in recreation and sports management.

Why I chose Utah Tech: “I chose Utah Tech because the coaches and players all come together as one.”
